Oh oh here we go again with " da wheel"  lol the wheel was never used to build the pyramids in Egypt or the Pyramids in the Sudan. Asians actually introduced the wheel to Africans, you can read about it in your bible where it mentions Ethiopian chariots. One of the oldest chariot horses were found in Sudan 3k years ago as they were famous for their horses.

Who invented agriculture ? Well lets see West Africans were farming over over 5k years ago. Both Europe and Africa received domesticated animals from Asia. Pigs, Sheep, goats and cattle from the near east and chicken from south east Asia. Its funny yall talk about agriculture when yall took 15 million Africans from Africa to do your agriculture work. 

Did Africa invent boats? One of the oldest boats in the world is found in West Africa, and we know Nubians and Egyptians and East Africans were using boats.

Africans were all over Europe and Asia. Europeans didn't Explore they colonized and exterminated in search for anything that would make them wealthy.

English is clearly the language forced upon us, that's so pathetic.
 
Americas
genocide by disease war etc over 50 million native Americans dead.
Asia
India famine caused over 50 million deaths.
Europe
ww1 and ww2 100 million deaths in 10 years.
Africa
Slave trade and colonization by europeans in Africa easily another 40 to 50 million dead or suffering.

And you know thats not including countless other problems yall created for others like the Opium wars with China and the massacres of Aboriginals.
 
Sir yall hands are dripping with blood while yall boast about what yall have done for the world.  You can keep that lol

content:
It was my 1st solo trip abroad. I was SICK on the flight, but I had to see if I could survive a year solo. 

1 solo trip to CR would lead to places like Egypt, Peru& Kenya.

1 yr would become 6.

A few IG posts would become Marriott, Delta, etc. partnerships as a content creator https://t.co/BOtVPcvkwZ

Of course Canada is broken, for at least three reasons well-illustrated by the China affair.

First, Canada has a more incestuous governing class than Ptolemaic Egypt.

Second, the combination of mass immigration and sixty years of deliberate cultural destruction have left us without any coherent national narrative. 

Third, the unique political geography of Canada allow that inbred political class to divide and rule, more or less indefinitely.
